<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://v020u46eff.maximumasp.com/AODB/">v020u46eff.maximumasp.com/AODB/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
Which DOES give the 'hidden' MA requirement to Multi with Fists (as 'attribute - Martial Arts') <br>
<br>
<br>
Claws - To Dual/To Equip <br>
<br>
Rat (1) 126/5 <br>
Rat (50) 178/224 <br>
Weasel (51) 179/229 <br>
Weasel (100) 364/448 <br>
Badger (101) 369/453 <br>
Badger (150) 637/672 <br>
Tiger (151) 643/677 <br>
Tiger (199) 905/892 &lt;--- Here's the problem, folks! <br>
Bear (200) 911/896 <br>
<br>
So, all claws Badger or lower, will take less MA to dual than to wield. In the middle of the Tiger range, it crosses over, and takes more to dual than to wield. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uskipsanders.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkipSanders</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#660000>(8/24/02 10:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2048.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Also, Initiative Update from AntiGuardians forums</span><hr size=1> krneki @ 2002-08-03 09:15  <br>
It works like this: <br>
<br>
(melee/ranged/physical Initiative) <br>
With 0 initiative and you agg-def bar at 75% you will fire at the rate the weapon says in the description. For every 600 init it reduces the attack speed by 1 sec and for every 600 init YOU SPEND (buffed/debuffed,item increased/decreased initiative DOESN'T afect recharge or increased init due to ability bonus)IPs for recharge speed gets reduced by 2 sec. If you set you agg-def from 100% to 50% 1 sec gets added to your attack and recharge speed and from 100% to 0% 2 sec get added to your attack and recharge. Speed cap is at 1 sec attack, 1 sec recharge. <br>
<br>
(NanoC Initative) <br>
With 0 initiative and you agg-def at 25% you will execute at the rate it says in the nano's description. The problem is unlike for other initiatives NanoC init only has THREE agg-def positions 0%, 1-99% and 100%, so the 25% is a theoretical value (I dunno maybe that's a bug). For every 200 NanoC init your attack speed gets reduced by 1 sec, recharge remains unchanged. By setting you agg-def from 100% to 1-99%, 1 sec gets added to your attack speed and nothing to recharge. From 100% to 0% 2 sec gets added to your attack speed and nothing to recharge. Speed cap is at 0 sec attack and recharge is whatever the description in the nano says. <br>
<br>
Also to note is that Initiative buffs/debuffs (or items such as crit scopes or TIM Hud) don't afect recharge speed, but only attack speed. This is what mainly caused confusion what really initiatives do.  <br>
